      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHALLOW SALLY (7) was strongly supported last start when a short priced favourite and duly saluted winning by 4.5 lengths at Geelong in a handy 22.46. Draws out wide but goes well at this distance. Winner at her latest appearance in the quickest time on the card. The one to beat again. CONROY PARK (2) last appeared when too good (23.26) over 400m at Geelong on July 4. Resumes after finishing seventh (23.26) at Geelong over 400m 11 months ago. Solid record at the distance winning two races. Will go close here with a clear run. ASTON FRANCESCA (4) started big odds last time but hit the ground running with a slick early split, giving a sight but fading out of it to finish fourth (22.30) at this track over 390m. Likely to play a prominent role. MAJOR WAIT (1) can measure up with the right run.",
